<section id="CardCounting">

	<h2>List limits and card counting</h2>

	<p>Place a limit on how many cards a list can contain, or simply display how many cards there are on each list.</p>

	<p>Limiting a list can help you plan your workload and focus on current tasks. Seeing how many cards there are can help when there are so many that the last card disappears off the end of the screen.</p>

	<p>You can add a limit to a list by putting a number in square brackets in the list title, e.g. <kbd class="tag">Doing&nbsp;[3]</kbd>. When cards are added that take the list over that limit, a notice will be displayed at the top of the list. To add a simple card count to a list without applying a limit, tag it with <kbd class="tag">#count</kbd> (not necessary if you enable the <i>All lists</i> option below). These features must be enabled before you can use them.</p>

	<div class="standard-options">
		<div>
			<h3>Enable list limits and card counting</h3>
			<p>Default: off</p>
		</div>
		<option-widget>
			<input type="checkbox" class="options-input" id="CountEnableWIP" name="CountEnableWIP" data-dependents='["MoreWIPOptions"]'>
			<label for="CountEnableWIP">
				Limits &amp; Card count
			</label>
		</option-widget>
	</div>

	<div id="MoreWIPOptions">

		<h3>More options</h3>

		<div class="standard-options">
			<div>
				<h4>Count cards on all lists</h4>
				<p>When this is enabled, cards will be counted on lists without needing to add the <kbd>#count</kbd> tag.</p>
				<p>Default: off</p>
			</div>
			<option-widget>
				<input type="checkbox" class="options-input" id="CountAllCards" name="CountAllCards">
				<label for="CountAllCards">
					All lists
				</label>
			</option-widget>
		</div>

		<div class="standard-options">
			<div>
				<h4>Enable manual points on cards</h4>
				<p>When enabled, you can change how much a card is worth by adding a number in square brackets to the card text. You can also specify zero if you don’t want a card to be counted. Header and Separator cards are not counted. Other extensions for Trello can sometimes prevent this option from working.</p>
				<p>Default: off</p>
			</div>
			<option-widget>
				<input type="checkbox" class="options-input" id="CountEnablePointsOnCards" name="CountEnablePointsOnCards" data-dependents='["CountHideManualCardPoints"]'>
				<label for="CountEnablePointsOnCards">
					Points on cards
				</label>
			</option-widget>
		</div>

		<div class="standard-options">
			<div>
				<h4>Hide points in card text</h4>
				<p>If this box and “Points on cards” are enabled, manual card points will be hidden.</p>
				<p><strong>⚠️ Note:</strong> this feature can interfere with other extensions for Trello that read or change card text, and vice versa. Disabling it should remove the conflict.</p>
				<p>Default: off</p>
			</div>
			<option-widget>
				<input type="checkbox" class="options-input" id="CountHideManualCardPoints" name="CountHideManualCardPoints">
				<label for="CountHideManualCardPoints">
					Hide card points
				</label>
			</option-widget>
		</div>

	</div>

</section>
